# Commit Message Emoji Usage

## Description
Defines the required emoji usage in commit messages based on the commit type.

## Rule
Each commit type has an associated emoji that must be used:
- `feat`: ✨ (sparkles)
- `fix`: 🐛 (bug)
- `test`: ✅ (check mark)
- `chore`: 🔧 (wrench)
- `refactor`: ♻️ (recycle)

## Examples
✅ Valid:
```
feat(ABC-123): ✨ Add new feature
fix(XYZ-987): 🐛 Fix bug
test(QWE-456): ✅ Add tests
chore(DEV-100): 🔧 Update dependencies
refactor(OPS-321): ♻️ Improve code structure
```

❌ Invalid:
```
feat(ABC-123): 🐛 Add new feature
fix(XYZ-987): ✨ Fix bug
feat(ABC-123): Add new feature
fix(XYZ-987): 🐞 Fix bug
```

## Notes
- Must include exactly one emoji
- Emoji must match the commit type
- Must have a space after the emoji
- Cannot use alternative emojis for the same meaning
